        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 26 at 6:25PM EDT by NWS Charleston WV</headline>
        <description>At 625 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Chattaroy, or 8 miles north of Williamson, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Delbarton, Mount Gay-Shamrock, Holden, Kermit, Naugatuck,
Verdunville, Dingess, Myrtle, Lenore, Breeden, and Switzer.

This includes Route 119 between mile markers 1 and 29.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
